@NicholasKreidberg That code `function isEmpty(object) { for(var i in object) { return true; } return false; }` got to be corrected after 11 years. 

Here's the correction: 

`function isEmpty(obj) {
    return !(() => {
        for (const i in obj) {
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    })();
}`

Alernatively: 

`function isObjectEmpty(obj) {
    for (const i in obj) return false;

    return true;
}`

